      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PINCER MOVEMENT (5) looks primed for a good run on debut following a nice trial with Pike in the saddle for his last two outings. Pike comes down to ride for the Grantham barn and the draw makes things easier for him. Both siblings are winners and he can notch up a debut victory. SEA OF GALILEE (2) flew home over the mile at this track last start following a 1.2L defeat over this course and distance two starts ago. The wide draw is a niggle, but his recent form stacks right up and he can put his best foot forward yet again. CROMBIE (1) was only 1.2L off the winner most recently over the mile last time out as a $41 chance. Drawn wider this time, but he showed good early speed most recently and he can feature on the quick turnaround. LONG REIGN (8) is better than she showed last time out and can improve getting out in trip today. SOPHISTRY (9) can improve on the last start effort.",
